comment.body:
the beauty of my backwardation trade is that
if long-end vega goes up = i win, (like market says 'higher for longer' on oil prices)
if short-end vega goes down = I win (like price rangebounds, or threat diminishes)
small loss only if short-end vega spike due to like strait closure...

but as refineries get hit, that forms a cap on the convexity

